To incorporate a new library for scientific computing in Rust and then embed the precalculations in Python, you could take the following steps:

In Rust, let's assume the library is called `scipy-rs` and it has a new function `precalculate_stats`:

```rust
// Rust code in lib.rs

use scipy_rs::precalculate_stats;  // assuming scipy_rs is our new library

// A function to run the calculation using the new library
pub fn do_precise_calculation() -> Result<f64, &'static str> {
    precalculate_stats()
        .map_err(|_| "Precalculation error occurred")
}

#[no_mangle]
pub extern "C" fn precalculations() -> f64 {
    match do_precise_calculation() {
        Ok(value) => value,
        Err(_) => 0.0, // Return a default value in case of error
    }
}
```

